 control text changes by authorized user/authors',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,'current','development','2013-05-01',NULL,2013,0,'LealtadCard','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'TaylorMadeTraffic','TaylorMadeTraffic',NULL,'Native Android SDK, Java, Facebook API, Chord Framework, All-Share Framework','ecommerce, marketing, analytics','TaylorMadeTraffic','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter= Sam Taylor\'> Sam Taylor</a>: Business Development','The promotions could be sent via SMS or Galaxy\'s Chord Framework. The interface and CMS is still in development','Lealtad card is a tool for independent retailers to publish and track promotions, along with their returned value and cost. For consumers, LealtadCard provides a way to search nearby promotions and publish their own controlled requests for good deals.','<em>A virtual marketplace for independent retailers to publish and track promotions, along with their return-on-investment (ROI).</em>\n                    <p>Customers can search promotions and publish their own requests to nearby retailers for special deals. The marketplace is focused on private offers only valid for a few hours.</p>','<ul class=\'alphalist\'>\n                            <li>$1/month for store owners to view customers data and analytics</li>\n                            <li>$1/month for store owners to send 100 private discount offers per month</li>\n                            <li>$1/month for store owners to public 10 public market ads per month</li>\n                            <li>Design &amp; Development services for more engaging mobile ads and promotions</li>\n                            <li>Build interactive and engaging maps for malls</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'expenselist\'>\n                            <li>15% design</li>\n                            <li>50% development</li>\n                            <li>25% sales</li>\n                            <li>10% hardware</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'datelist\'>\n                            <li>6 months: virtual marketplace with promotional builder and search/publishing by GPS location</li>\n                            <li>1 year: in malls with maps and directory listings</li>\n                        </ul>','<a class=\"snapshots mask0x250 fancybox\" href=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/lealtad/research/android-apps-loyalty-card.jpg\" data-fancybox-group=\"lealtadcard\" >\n                            <img src=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/lealtad/research/android-apps-loyalty-card_400x0.jpg\" />\n                            <div class=\"blackOutFadeBG\"></div>\n                        </a>\n                        <a class=\"snapshots mask0x250 fancybox\" href=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/lealtad/research/citypoints.jpg\" data-fancybox-group=\"lealtadcard\" >\n                            <img src=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/lealtad/research/citypoints_400x0.jpg\" />\n                            <div class=\"blackOutFadeBG\"></div>\n                        </a>',NULL),(11,'current','development','2012-11-01','2013-01-01',2012,2013,'Track Authority - CodeIgniter Website / API','','http://trackauthoritymusic.com',NULL,NULL,'TaylorMadeTraffic','Track Authority Music',NULL,'PHP, CodeIgniter, mySQL, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, Bash, Facebook API','music, events, gaming','TaylorMadeTraffic, Track Authority Music','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End, Business Development. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Drew Williams\'>Drew Williams</a>: Business Development','The website runs in a LAMP environment, and is highly optimized by several Bash scripts\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                    <li>One is run from a CRON to use ImageMagick for cropping and resizing images based on automated cue table maintained when a size or shape is requested that has not yet been cut.</li>\r\n                    <li>Another is for re-indexing the music catalogue - of 20,000 songs and growing. It extends a tool called Beets to correct mp3 meta-data, download artwork and lyrics, and determine sound-wave averages such as BPM (beats-per-minute) and Replay Gain (used to determine average encoded decibel volume of the sound wave).</li>\r\n                    <li>The backend system also includes an asynchronous email service which I linked seamlessly to the front-end webpage templates with a CSS inliner script.</li>\r\n                    <li>The site scales very well to all screen widths above 320 pixels wide, but I am well underway with a native Android version of the player with 0-100 scale music ratings to refine the rotation of songs.</li>\r\n                    <li>It also includes a CodeIgniter plug-in that manages translations of system copy and user-generated content, with version controlling text changes by authorized user/authors.</li>\r\n                </ul>','An online and mobile game that rewards high rated users with free music, gift certificates, concert tickets and cash.','<em>An online and mobile game for music lovers to play, exchange, and reward musical taste.</em>\n                    <p>Highly rated users are rewarded with free music, gift certificates, concert tickets and cash from sponsors and partners</p>\n                    <p>The platform supports three ways to play and win. Each starts with a playlist theme, such as \'Rise And Shine\': Songs for My Alarm Clock.</p>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>1. Group members enter a song that suits the theme</li>\n                        <li>2. Group members list and rate each other\'s songs</li>\n                        <li>3. After two weeks, the person who submitted the highest rated song wins</li>\n                    </ul>\n                    <p>This game can easily be incorporated as a promotional vehicle for concert tours. For example, if that alarm clock was Jay-Z\'s, the options are countless for prizes from tickets to backstage passes and all links during the competition promote the concert</p>','<ul class=\'alphalist\'>\n                            <li>concert ticket re-sales (3-5% fee)</li>\n                            <li>$1 - $10 subscriptions to ad-free listening and extra playlist features</li>\n                            <li>Concert ticket promotions, advertising and sales</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'expenselist\'>\n                            <li>15% design</li>\n                            <li>70% development</li>\n                            <li>10% sales</li>\n                            <li>5% accounting</li>\n                            <li>5% legal</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'datelist\'>\n                            <li>6 months: mobile app &amp; site complete</li>\n                        </ul>','<a class=\"snapshots mask0x250 fancybox\" href=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/ta/research/android-apps-music-games.jpg\" data-fancybox-group=\"trackauthority\" >\n                            <img src=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/ta/research/android-apps-music-games_400x0.jpg\" />\n                            <div class=\"blackOutFadeBG\"></div>\n                        </a>','<ul class=\'marketresearch\'>\n                            <li>NO online concert ticket vendors also support extensive music stations or playlists</li>\n                            <li>Concert Ticket sold 52 million (2011) - <a class=\'sourceLink\' href=\"http://www.statisticbrain.com/concert-ticket-sale-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\">source</a></li>\n                            <li>Concert Ticket Revenue 3.1 Billion USD (2011) - <a class=\'sourceLink\' href=\"http://www.statisticbrain.com/concert-ticket-sale-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\">source</a></li>\n                            <li>Pollstar lists 10,859 touring artists, 71,823 Events - <a class=\'sourceLink\' href=\"http://money.futureofmusic.org/how-many-musicians-are-there/\" target=\"_blank\">source</a></li>\n                            <li><a href=\"http://musicbrainz.org/statistics\" target=\'_blank\'>musicbrainz.org/statistics</a></li>\n                            <li><a class=\'sourceLink\' href=\"http://www.ascap.com/about/\" target=\"_blank\">ASCAP</a>: 435,000 composters, songwriters, music publishers</li>\n                            <li><a class=\'sourceLink\' href=\"http://www.bmi.com/about\" target=\"_blank\">BMI</a>: 500,000 composters, songwriters, music publishers</li>                            \n                        </ul>'),(12,'current','development','2013-07-01','2013-12-01',2013,2013,'ID Dashboard','','http://analytics.idinteractive.co',NULL,NULL,'ID Interactive','ID Interactive',NULL,'PHP, CodeIgniter, mySQL, AJAX, JavaScript, Google Visualization API, Facebook API, YouTube API, Twitter API, Laraval, CSS3, HTML5','analytics','ID Interactive','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Juan Ruiz\'>Juan Ruiz</a>: Business Development. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Claudia Huertas\'>Claudia Huertas</a>: Business Development. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Alejandra Farfan\'>Alejandra Farfan</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=David Duran\'>David Duran</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=John Parra\'>John Parra</a>: QA. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Mauricio Zambrano\'>Mauricio Zambrano</a>: UX. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Catalina Molina\'>Catalina Molina</a>: UX','Over 45 Google Visualization Graphs can be created in less than 10 seconds. By entering just a few project goals in the form of KPIs (Key Performance Indicators), graphs are automatically colorized in to indicate how they are performing. Project & account managers can also using a simple CMS built within the reports to comment on specific metrics, add headers, group graphics, change sizes and drill on the data through AJAX connections to all the original API services. The permissions matrix is controlled per client, brand, and project with 6 levels of access, including publishing public reports with encrypted URLs. The codebase is in CodeIgnitor 2.','The tool automates monthly reports due clients, by aggregating data from all active marketing channels or installed tracking tools, such as Twitter, Facebook Insights, Google Analytics and, YouTube.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,'current','development','2013-06-01','2013-07-01',2013,2013,'Sedal Rizos','','https://apps.facebook.com/sedalrizos/','http://fbtabs.imagendigital.co/unilever/sedal/surprise/',NULL,'Sedal','ID Interactive',NULL,'PHP, Slim Framework, mySQL, AJAX, JavaScript, Facebook API','fashion, gaming','Sedal, ID Interactive','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Zandro Gil\'>Zandro Gil</a>: Design.  <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Luisa Vicaría Azuero\'>Luisa Vicaría Azuero</a>: Account Manager.  <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Front-End, Back-End.  <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Fabian Mariño\'>Fabian Mariño</a>: Front-End.  <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Natalia Uribe\'>Natalia Uribe</a>: Project Management.  <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Jimmy Rodriguez\'>Jimmy Rodriguez</a>: QA','Another quick campaign application to generate FanPage likes. In order to compete, users were required to like Sedal\'s FanPage, complete registration, and upload videos, images, or a tip on maintaining their curly hair (ideally using Sedal products;). Voting was validated by IP, user agent, and session, while video uploads were POST\'d directly to a public YouTube channel using their PHP SDK. The project extended ID\'s fork of the Slim PHP Framework. I personally found more hurdles than helpers in the tightly namespaced codebase and it\'s odd use of closures for routing/controllers.','A curly-hair competition for a $250 shopping spree',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,'current','development','2013-11-01','2013-12-01',2013,2013,'Oreo Navidad','','http://www.ganaoreo.com',NULL,NULL,'Oreo','ID Interactive',NULL,'PHP, mySQL, JavaScript','gaming','Oreo, ID Interactive','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Cristopher Allen Lara\'>Cristopher Allen Lara</a>: Design. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Oscar Gil\'>Oscar Gil</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Sharon Lewis\'>Sharon Lewis</a>: Account Manager. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Jimmy Rodriguez\'>Jimmy Rodriguez</a>: QA. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=John Parra\'>John Parra</a>: QA','A search against the 20 million codes took .00020 seconds, and the site supported business rules such as Catpcha when a user searched more than 12 times in a day. I also included several backend tracking tools and an automated QA tester to simulate varying degrees of traffic, code searches, and minimum probabilities.','IDinteractive builds marketing platforms for a long list of great clients with creative projects and campaigns. The campaign was based on 20 million codes printed on Oreo packages throughout Colombia. There were 5 types of prizes to win in varying amounts with a total of 285 to give.  No one code could be considered a winner in advance, and the prizes should be distributed evenly throughout the ~60 day campaign. I wrote the probability to be related to the average number of people playing daily and distributed all prizes - by number and type - evenly until the last day.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(15,'current','development','2002-11-01','2004-12-01',2002,2004,'Collectiv LLC','','http://www.collectiv.com/','http://www.collectiv.com/events.php',NULL,'Collectiv LLC','Collectiv LLC',NULL,NULL,'music, art, events','Collectiv LLC','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Jamie Williams\'>Jamie Williams</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Eli Taylor\'>Eli Taylor</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Drew Williams\'>Drew Williams</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Tommy Goodwin\'>Tommy Goodwin</a>: Project Management',NULL,'<ul>\n                <li>The Collectiv was born in the summer of 2001 in Oakland, CA. Our organization was founded by A. Williams, aka Sokrates, with a mission to \"empower the Hip Hop community through education and entrepreneurship.\" We pursue this mission by sponsoring a diverse range of programs with distinct yet cooperative goals. We work with young entrepreneurs, activists and artists to design financially viable programs that will provide new opportunities for empowerment. We seek to create the perfect environment for turning an idea into impact.</li>\n                <li>The Collectiv currently sponsors three programs, Collectiv Records, Collectiv Arts &amp; Entertainment and Collectiv Foundation. Each of these programs occupies a distinct niche within the Hip Hop community.</li>\n                </ul>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(16,'current','development','2009-05-01','2012-07-01',2009,2012,'Healthline Navigator','','http://www.healthline.com/corporate/navigator/prod/demo.html',NULL,NULL,'Healthline Networks','Healthline Networks',NULL,'Java, Spring, Oracle, JavaScript, JSONP','health, marketing','Healthline Networks','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=AJ Chen\'>AJ Chen</a>: Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Steve Jackson\'>Steve Jackson</a>: Back-End','<ul>\n                    <li>Navigator is a cross-domain script tag used to inject contextual ads and content onto any web page from a single line of JavaScript.</li>\n                    <li>The system supports up to 60 requests per second including tracking pixels and over 50,000 SQL inserts batched daily through an asynchronous SQL loader. (Clients included healthline.com, sharecare.com, health.yahoo.net, drugs.com and others)</li>\n                    <li>Units can be injected on-load and by user-engagement, directly on the page, or by hyper-linking keywords in the page source. Keywords can be pre-selected during the crawling process or via a client-side DOM scanner searching common semantics and other ad tags running simultaneously. This allows well targeted advertising services without a backend processor for contextualization</li>\n                    <li>It can automatically detect appropriate ad placement via another DOM scanner that measures element\'s amount of text, dimensions, DOM structure and tag types. It also can be more tightly controlled via Dashboard described below.</li>\n                    <li>Injected content - where hyper-links remain on the host website - can be placed to provide additional navigation tools for the user. However this requires pre-indexing the client\'s entire site. This process is targeted, cued and controlled by Navigator and its Dashboard, described below.</li>\n                </ul>','A Contextual Enrichment Tool of Rich-Media Health Information and Ads.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(17,'current','development','2009-05-01','2012-07-01',2009,2012,'Healthline Dashboard','','http://nav.healthline.com/healthstat/nav/dashboard/login',NULL,NULL,'Healthline Networks','Healthline Networks',NULL,'Java, Spring, Oracle, JavaScript, AJAX, jQuery Mobile','health, analytics, marketing','Healthline Networks','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End','<ul>\n                    <li>Dashboard aids in backend debugging of the Healthline Taxonomy and search decisions. It also provides the crawler additional controls for prioritizing areas of the page to parse, skip, and flag for changes or inter-linking .</li>\n                    <li>Through Dashboard you can rebuild any webpage within a proxy environment on Healthline servers in order to install, test, and demonstrate Navigation functionality on any URL</li>\n                </ul>','Dashboard is an all-in-one Content-Management-System, Reporting, and Ad Configuration tool. It controls where, when and why to inject ads or content in webpages. It also allows reviewing Navigator, healthSTAT, and internal crawler\'s performance across various installations.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(18,'current','development','2009-05-01','2012-07-01',2009,2012,'Healthline computeQA','','http://www.healthline.com/corporate/navigator/prod/crawler.html?domain=healthline',NULL,NULL,'Healthline Networks','Healthline Networks',NULL,'WebSQL-lite, JavaScript, Google Chrome Extension, jQuery Mobile, LocalStorage','analytics','Healthline Networks','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End','<ul>\n                    <li>A Google Chrome Extension and browser-based Crawler to automate QA of both source code, flash ads, any JavaScript installation.</li>\n                    <li>Builds automated reports on how pages are categorized by many different engines and APIs, while tracking the web of links between each page. Everything is stored in SQLite LocalStorage via Lawnchair. Ex. healthline.com/corporate/navigator/stage/crawler.html?domain=sharecare  or ?domain=healthline (both take a while to load all 30K rows)</li>\n                    <li>Takes .jpg screenshots of every page crawled. It can also first render watermarks or outline all areas of the page by targeting categories for easier review &amp; debugging.</li>\n                </ul>','Automated Quality Assurance & Monitoring Through Interactive, Intelligent Browser-Based Crawling.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(19,'current','development','2013-08-01',NULL,2013,0,'Studio En Vivo','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'TaylorMadeTraffic','TaylorMadeTraffic',NULL,'Native Android SDK, Java, Chord Framework, All-Share Framework','music, gaming','TaylorMadeTraffic','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End','The music is shared a runtime using Galaxy\'s All-Share and Chord Framework. This internal project was never completed but I still have hopes to revive it with the right team. Please reach out if you\'re interested in working together.','A mobile beat machine to create and share music with friends','<em>The first mobile beat machine to create and share music with friends in real-time.</em> \n                    <p>Like most similar apps, StudioEnVivo allows customizing your keyboard with sounds and laying background tracks as you play.</p>\n                    <p>However, unlike any other app, you can play simultaneously with other friends via Bluetooth / Chord / All-Share frameworks and finally stitch together your recordings for a collaborative composition.</p>\n                    <p>As users upload their compositions to the cloud, the social aspect of sharing and comparing compositions are endless...</p>','<ul class=\'alphalist\'>\n                            <li>$1 download ad-free version</li>\n                            <li>$5 download ad-free with offline access and cloud storage</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'expenselist\'>\n                            <li>30% design</li>\n                            <li>70% development</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'datelist\'>\n                           <li>6  months: mobile app site complete</li>\n                        </ul>','<a class=\"snapshots mask0x250 fancybox\" href=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/studioenvivo/research/android-app-electrum-drum-machine-sampler.jpg\" data-fancybox-group=\"studioenvivo\" >\n                            <img src=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/studioenvivo/research/android-app-electrum-drum-machine-sampler_400x0.jpg\" />\n                            <div class=\"blackOutFadeBG\"></div>\n                        </a>\n                        <a class=\"snapshots mask0x250 fancybox\" href=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/studioenvivo/research/android-app-drum-machine.jpg\" data-fancybox-group=\"studioenvivo\" >\n                            <img src=\"/wwwroot/images/sites/studioenvivo/research/android-app-drum-machine_400x0.jpg\" />\n                            <div class=\"blackOutFadeBG\"></div>\n                        </a>',NULL),(20,'current','development','2010-05-01','2011-07-01',2010,2011,'Known Your Numbers','','http://www.healthline.com/corporate/widgets/OptumTools/index.html','http://www.healthline.com/corporate/widgets/OptumTools/demo.html',NULL,'OptumHealth','Healthline Networks',NULL,'Flex, AS3','health','OptumHealth, Healthline Networks','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Matt Sperling\'>Matt Sperling</a>: Design. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Front-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Steve Berley\'>Steve Berley</a>: Project Management','The business requirements insisted that the tool be distributable as a single self-contained file which could be easily reskinned for other brands. It was not clear if their target devices would run Java (Applets), but certain they had browsers with Flash, so used Flex and AS3.','A set of 30 health assessment and preparation tools developed for OptumHealth, a division of UnitedHealth Group',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(21,'current','development','2010-05-01','2011-07-01',2010,2011,'Munchie Madness','','http://www.healthline.com/tournaments/healthy-frozen-dinners-tournament','http://www.healthline.com/channel/healthy-fast-food-video',NULL,'Healthline Networks','Healthline Networks',NULL,'Flex, AS3','health, food','Healthline Networks','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Matt Sperling\'>Matt Sperling</a>: Design. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Front-End','These two links are just a few of the very interactive microsites / applications I built for Healthline\'s editorial team or sponsoring partners.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(22,'current','development','2009-05-01','2009-07-01',2009,2009,'Elite Wedding Locations','','http://www.weddinglocation.com','http://www.weddinglocation.com/clientpass/index.php',NULL,'Elite Wedding Locations','Noospheric LLC',NULL,'AJAX, AS3, Flex, PHP, mySQL, JavaScript','analytics, marketing','Elite Wedding Locations, Noospheric LLC','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Jacquas Habra\'>Jacquas Habra</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Kevin Kent\'>Kevin Kent</a>: Project Management. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=James McCorkle\'>James McCorkle</a>: Project Management','This system included 3 levels of access with top level administrators being able to change cost values per account or property, receive notifications upon account logins, and scheduling custom reports to be email at any frequency or time span, to anyone. The system provides complete drilling capabilities on any data set for any time frame; and populates both Flex graphs and DHTML tables and charts with a single click.','A reporting system for advertisers to view site traffic, user inquiries on their properties, and return-on-investment figures.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(23,'current','development','2009-07-01','2009-08-01',2009,2009,'Black Panther Party','','http://www.blackpanther.org','http://bpp.taylormadetraffic.com/',NULL,'Huey P. Newton Foundation','Huey P. Newton Foundation',NULL,'AS3, PHP, CodeIgniter, mySQL, AJAX, JavaScript, CSS3','education, ecommerce','Huey P. Newton Foundation','','Eli implemented the Google Language API (php) to translate entire site and individual articles to nearly any language using an asynchronous AJAX cue-engine to control http request priorities, frequency and timeouts. Extended open source CMS OpenCart with configuration options to map and re-stylize all products and profiles','Design & developed a unique interface for navigating articles, essays, events, and new program initiatives. This was a volunteer project with early ambitions for a commercial joint venture. It fell apart over internal issues.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(24,'current','development','2009-03-01','2009-10-01',2009,2009,'ChartMedica','','http://www.chartmedica.com',NULL,NULL,'ChartMedica LLC','Noospheric LLC',NULL,'AS3, Flex, PHP, mySQL','health','ChartMedica LLC','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Roy\'>Roy</a>: Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=David\'>David</a>: Back-End','Developed Flex-based interface for a patient\'s medical records system. Extended the server-side services to generate dynamic PDF (fpdf) of records and record requests. PDFs were then automatically faxed to physician offices when 5 available incoming fax lines to parse and import records (using myFax.com API). The application also included other libraries and components such as e-signing with Flex and hospital searches by location and specialty.','Features included an advanced pdf viewing tool, autocompletes searching over 600K records, and automated faxing via MyFax API.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(25,'current','development','2008-09-01','2009-02-01',2008,2009,'The Means','','http://www.TheMeans.info','http://www.TheMeans.info/_dev/web40.php','1','TaylorMadeTraffic','Berkeley High School',NULL,'AS3, PHP, mySQL, AJAX, JavaScript, CSS3','education, e-learning','TaylorMadeTrafficTaylorMadeTraffic, Berkeley High School','<a href=\'/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor\'>E.A.Taylor</a>: Design, Front-End, Back-End. <a href=\'/team?qtfilter=Biko Eisen-Martin\'>Biko Eisen-Martin</a>: Product Development','UI Tools include tinyMCE text editor, advance sourcing maps, and multi-category search options','<p>A vision from <a href=\"http://www.google.com.co/search?q=biko+eisen-martin\" target=\"_blank\">Biko Eisen-Martin</a> for his students at <a href=\"http://bhs.berkeleyschools.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Berkeley High School</a> to create a tool for teachers and students to collaborate and compete in the writing process. Modeled after a traditional newsroom, students and teachers would be able to develop assignments, work on multiple versions of a story, share ideas within the class, and more. \r\n                    We built a prototype site that supported a semester of great essays still worth reading, but the project lost momentum as we both moved cities.</p>\r\n                    <p>This project\'s greatest potential was in a version-controller for teachers to review, grade and provide feedback on student\'s essays, while peer reviews drove friendly competition between writer and school rankings.</p>\r\n                    <p>If you work in Education or feel something like this could help your classroom or school district, please email me. I\'d love bring it back to life in our spare time.</p>','<em>A platform for High School newspapers that allows students to collaborate and share their academic and athletic achievements.</em>\n                <p>Students and teachers would be able to develop assignments, work on multiple versions of a story, share ideas within the class, and more.</p>            \n                <p>The competitive advantage of this site is in the version-controlling system that allows peer-reviews, teachers edit, and the student\'s versions to all be tracked independently. In addition, the system would include tools for simplifying footnotes and sources, and to include photos and links.</p>','<ul class=\'alphalist\'>\n                            <li>License to private schools &amp; learning institutions</li>\n                            <li>Donate to the public school system, gain publicity and intimate access to the youth market, along with tax deductions from donation.</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'expenselist\'>\n                            <li>20% design</li>\n                            <li>60% development</li>\n                            <li>20% sales & support</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'datelist\'>\n                            <li>6 months: in 2 schools with basic text-editor and version controlling</li>\n                            <li>1 year: in schools with full-feature text-editor and multi-user version controlling</li>\n                        </ul>','<ul class=\'